Craftsman Tractor to Make Appearance at Detroit Auto Show<br/><br/>The <a href="http://en.pan.netcom/go/out/url=-aHR0cDovL3d3dy5jYXJsb2NhdGUuY29tL0Jsb2cvcG9zdC8yMDExLzEyLzI3L0F1dG8tTmV3cy1Sb3VuZHVwLUxvb2tpbmctRm9yd2FyZC10by0yMDEyLmFzcHg_" target="_blank">2012 North American International Auto Show</a>is set to feature techy concepts, record-breaking muscle cars, uber-luxury vehicles of all types: and a fully-loaded Craftsman tractor. 
<br /><br />This unconventional entry won’t be competing against Smart’s new concept or the new Mercedes SL, though it’s sure to be both economic and stylish. The CTX Tractor Series will be on display as a marketing entry: Craftsman is one of the Detroit show’s sponsors.
<br /><br />The CTX will be the first tractor ever to appear at the auto show. According to Craftsman, the CTX is loaded with automotive-inspired features, such as cruise control and cup holders. The CTX is expected to debut in stores next month, and features a 30-horsepower Briggs &amp; Stratton engine. Craftsman says the tractor will be similar to many of the NAIAS cars in that it will be the &quot;best in its class.&quot;
